m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +1 {g|Encyclopedia:Speed}speed{/g} dwarven waraxe deals additional 9 {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g} on a successful {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical hit{/g} and grants its wielder the ability to cast flare {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} twice per day as a 1st level wizard.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This fine piece of equipment was crafted by dwarf Dragn, the {g|Encyclopedia:Skills}skillful{/g} blacksmith, appointed a court master.

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Cruel Elder Shocking Burst Dwarven Waraxe +5

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +1 dwarven waraxe deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d3{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Energy_Damage}acid damage{/g} on a hit.

While the wielder of this +3 dwarven waraxe is wielding a second weapon in another hand, whenever they confirm a {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical hit{/g} with it, they also make an additional {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack{/g} with the second weapon.

Whenever this +3 thundering dwarven waraxe is wielded by a dwarf, it grants the wielder a +2 inherent {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Armor_Class}AC{/g} and a +1 inherent bonus on {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack rolls{/g}.
This +4 dragon bane dwarven waraxe doubles any insight {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack{/g} and {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g} the wielder might have.

This +5 mithral necrotic dwarven waraxe grants its wielder a +4 morale {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} on {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack{/g} and {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage rolls{/g} against huge and bigger enemies.
This is a +1 cold iron ghost touch weapon.

This is a +3 brilliant energy heartseeker weapon. This weapon can tear the soul of a living enemy: whenever it lands a hit, it deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d6{/g} force {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This weapon was once the seat of Finnean's soul. Now that the soul of the Sarkorian Pathfinder has left the weapon, it has fallen silent forever.
